The paper deals with problems related to dominating sets in graphs, which are typically studied in the areas of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses approximability and inapproximability results, which are common topics in computational complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper introduces a new type of dominating set called an $f$-dominating set, which could potentially be of interest to researchers in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) who work on graph-based machine learning algorithms.
